{"count": 28687, "next": "https://api.acmi.net.au/creators/?page=2844", "previous": "https://api.acmi.net.au/creators/?page=2842", "results": [{"id": 7132, "name": "Luc Courchesne", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2710218, "title": "The Visitor: living by number [documentation]", "work_id": 108253, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": null, "date_of_death": null, "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "Luc Courchesne (Canada b.1952)\n\nLuc Courchesne began his explorations in interactive visitor-triggered video in 1984 when he co-authored Elastic Movies with Bill Seamen among others at MIT. He has since produced several installations including Encyclopaedia Chiaroscuro (1987), Portrait One (1990), Family Portrait (1993), Landscape One (1997), Passages (1998) and Rendezvous (1999). He has had a solo show at Museum of Modern Art in New York. These experiments with conversational interfaces have been elaborated to give the impression of communication between visitors and virtual beings. The video sequences are stored on laser-disc and displayed as reflections on a glass plate positioned directly above the video projection. Of late, Courchesne has tried to make a more closed sense of space, and to create a better sense of immersion. His latest work is with interactive devices set in a single-channel panoramic viewer, Panoscope 360, a doughnut-shaped anamorphic video, which gives a seamless image and uses voice for input. 'In expanding the field of view', writes Courchesne, 'immersive imaging frees the viewer's body and multiplies the possible points of view, [...] transforming spectators into visitors.'", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2025-03-11T23:27:12.222437+11:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "3a4a72a1-9693-40b5-a841-204c820ae163", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "110736", "external_references": [], "date_modified": "2025-03-11T23:27:12.222784+11:00"}, {"id": 7128, "name": "Maria-Fernanda Cardoso", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2711491, "title": "Chicken face", "work_id": 109208, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2710212, "title": "Cardoso Flea Circus", "work_id": 108252, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-08-11T15:22:54.183071+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "bc7e5ee4-4325-4798-bc1c-e700699a0aad", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "110731", "external_references": [], "date_modified": "2025-03-11T23:52:54.519083+11:00"}, {"id": 7127, "name": "Ross Harley", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2710210, "title": "Cardoso Flea Circus", "work_id": 108252, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-08-11T15:11:49.359219+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "ab6f153c-1806-4d1d-bf66-ddf561822027", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "110730", "external_references": [], "date_modified": "2025-03-11T23:26:52.414741+11:00"}, {"id": 7126, "name": "Eurydice Aroney", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2710176, "title": "Strange Cities", "work_id": 108248, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-08-14T10:52:57.944008+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "ca254b32-1a88-4050-8ce2-ce2d2866f424", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "110729", "external_references": [], "date_modified": "2025-03-11T23:25:01.656764+11:00"}, {"id": 7125, "name": "Tatiana Pentes", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2710173, "title": "Strange Cities", "work_id": 108248, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2710174, "title": "Strange Cities", "work_id": 108248, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2710175, "title": "Strange Cities", "work_id": 108248, "role": "writer", "role_id": 939, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "Tatiana Pentes graduated from the College of Fine Arts, University of New South Wales, (1995) with Master of Art (Media Arts : Film, Video, Sound and Multimedia). Strange Cities CD-Rom won Best Innovative/Artistic multimedia category, 2000 ATOM AWARDS, Australia; was promoted at the New Talent Pavilion, MILIA GAMES '99, Multimedia Festival, Cannes, France; exhibited in the 1999 EXPERIMENTA CD-Rom Exhibition, Australia, and dLux media arts, D.art 99, Artspace, Sydney Film Festival, (+ touring). The artist was successful in attaining an Australian Film Commission Multimedia Program of Assistance in January 1997, to develop an interactive script for the Strange Cities CD-Rom, and June 1997 received Production Funding to complete the project. The title was launched at SCA Gallery, Sydney College of the Arts, October 1999.", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2025-03-11T23:24:58.268476+11:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "87d1acc7-43db-42a1-a765-fe6d453f97fd", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "110728", "external_references": [{"id": 34409, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q120700024"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-11T23:24:58.268744+11:00"}, {"id": 7124, "name": "Magnetic Monster Video", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 1818798, "title": "Godzilla meets the Brady bunch the art of Maria Kozic", "work_id": 80291, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2710168, "title": "AstroTurf", "work_id": 108246, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T12:32:56.060285+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "45a8a027-f124-469a-9066-ce0d498d5273", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "1413", "external_references": [{"id": 40388, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q121315555"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-11T23:24:25.897683+11:00"}, {"id": 7123, "name": "Rod Bishop", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2261450, "title": "Salt, saliva, sperm and sweat (AFC)", "work_id": 83154, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2644668, "title": "ERA : the Educational Reform Association School (TEFC)", "work_id": 67224, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2121792, "title": "Body melt", "work_id": 85172, "role": "co-producer", "role_id": 915, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2710165, "title": "AstroTurf", "work_id": 108246, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T17:29:35.679260+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "f463d03c-a6b8-4b17-9c1e-4be9463d41f6", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "111702", "external_references": [{"id": 51197, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q121357898"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-11T23:24:19.321443+11:00"}, {"id": 7121, "name": "Ian Haig", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 771841, "title": "Godzilla meets the Brady bunch the art of Maria Kozic", "work_id": 80291, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2676434, "title": "Ecto plasmic baby fat provider", "work_id": 109880, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2710163, "title": "AstroTurf", "work_id": 108246, "role": "animator", "role_id": 497, "is_primary": false}, {"id": 2710161, "title": "AstroTurf", "work_id": 108246, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2710200, "title": "Trick or treat", "work_id": 108249, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2710206, "title": "K-Rad Man", "work_id": 108250, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2710215, "title": "Psycho samba", "work_id": 108251, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2710202, "title": "Trick or treat", "work_id": 108249, "role": "film maker", "role_id": 459, "is_primary": false}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "1964", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "Ian Haig works across media, from video, sculpture, drawing, technology based media and installation. Haig’s practice refuses to accept that the low and the base level are devoid of value and cultural meaning. His body obsessed themes can be seen throughout a large body of work over the last twenty years. Previous works have looked to the contemporary media sphere and its relationship to the visceral body, the degenerative aspects of pervasive new technologies, to cultural forms of fanaticism and cults, to ideas of attraction and repulsion, body horror, the defamiliarisation and confrontation of the human body.\n\nHis work has been exhibited in galleries and video/media festivals around the world. Including exhibitions at: The Australian Centre for Contemporary Art, Melbourne; The Ian Potter Museum of Art, Melbourne; The Experimental Art Foundation, Adelaide; The Australian Centre for the Moving Image, Melbourne; Gallery of Modern Art, Brisbane; The Museum of Modern Art, New York; Artec Biennale – Nagoya, Japan; Centre Georges Pompidou, Paris; China Millennium Monument Art Museum, Beijing; Museum Villa Rot, Burgrieden-Rot, Germany; The Havana Biennial, Cuba. In addition his video work has screened in over 150 festivals internationally including The Ann Arbor film festival, US and VideoBrasil, Sao Paulo, Brazil. In 2003 he received a fellowship from the New Media Arts Board of the Australia Council and in 2013 and 2017 he curated the video art shows Unco and Very Unco at The Torrance Art Museum in Los Angeles.\n\n[source: https://www.ianhaig.net/index.php?section=bio; last accessed 11.02.21]", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2025-03-11T23:27:10.821123+11:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "64cb4e76-7346-4665-b088-4bb1147d6531", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "110727", "external_references": [{"id": 39127, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q120308529"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-11T23:27:10.821336+11:00"}, {"id": 7119, "name": "Linda Dement", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2710151, "title": "In My Gash", "work_id": 108245, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2710144, "title": "Cyberflesh Girlmonster", "work_id": 108244, "role": "creator", "role_id": 968, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2513258, "title": "[Cyberflesh Girlmonster : publicity kit]", "work_id": 118606, "role": "artist", "role_id": 505, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-08-11T18:20:14.851910+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "4ea6b03c-438b-42e0-b827-d07ca988dc7f", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "110725", "external_references": [], "date_modified": "2025-03-11T23:23:42.843521+11:00"}, {"id": 7117, "name": "Michae